The management of the University of Ibadan (UI) has confirmed that the Governor of Edo State, Godwin Nogheghase Obaseki, attended the institution between 1976 and 1979. The National Chairman of the APC, Comrade Adams Oshiomhole, who has been feuding with Obaseki had on Tuesday expressed doubt over the governor’s certificate. The Registrar of UI, Mrs. Olubunmi O. Faluyi, in a statement, said the governor studied classics from the institution. The university said: “Mr. Godwin Nogheghase Obaseki, the Governor of Edo State, graduated from the University of Ibadan where he studied classics. Dear valued readers, subscribe to the Daily Trust e-paper to continue enjoying our diet of authoritative news. Kindly subscribe here “Mr. Obaseki gained admission to the university in 1976 and graduated in 1979 with a Second Class Honours, Lower Division. Records of his admission and graduation are intact in the archives of the university.” UI faults Oshiomhole, confirms Obaseki’s certificate Edo APC faction suspends Obaseki, deputy governor Edo governorship: Plot to disqualify Obaseki thickens